1
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:09,000
We speak of the guru principle,
or guru‒tattva in all of its manifestations.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,200
[Guru | Depth of Field at Infinity]

3
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,600
So, Śrīla Viśvanāth Cakravartī Ṭhākur,

4
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:25,700
and in one sense
the premiere guru song

5
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:32,300
the Gurv-aṣṭakam,
sung by all devotees, everyday.

6
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:38,500
sākṣād-dharitvena samasta-śāstrair
uktas tathā bhāvyata eva sadbhiḥ
 

7
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:44,200
kintu prabhor yaḥ priya eva tasya
vande guroḥ śrī-caraṇāravindam
 

8
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:52,210
So, we are told that 
our beginning conception

9
00:00:52,210 --> 00:01:01,160
sākṣād‒hari—directly Kṛṣṇa.
Kṛṣṇa is the focal point.

10
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:08,200
Like when you have 
in photography:

11
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:15,260
focus, near depth of field, 
other things.

12
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:22,070
There is also a type 
of depth of field called infinity.

13
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,030
So here we’re told,

14
00:01:24,030 --> 00:01:30,900
and Guru Mahārāj’s given
a perfect example,

15
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:37,000
and he says, just as let me
talk of the Himalayas, Himalaya,

16
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:42,820
the Everest is the supreme peak.

17
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:48,390
So, he said, 
“You’ll see that from …

18
00:01:48,390 --> 00:01:49,960
in one sense 
making your approach,

19
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:52,800
from the greatest distance 
you see Everest.

20
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:58,310
So, focused on Everest,
with Everest as your goal

21
00:01:58,310 --> 00:02:01,400
you make your approach.

22
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:07,900
But, the proof positive that
you are coming near to Everest

23
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,590
that you are going
in the right direction,

24
00:02:10,590 --> 00:02:15,880
is you will come in connection
with so many subordinate peaks,

25
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:20,000
which are surrounding Everest.

26
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,960
That you are coming
in their connection

27
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:26,800
means you are going 
in the right direction towards Everest.

28
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:33,520
The parallel being that
vāsudevaḥ sarvam iti

29
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,580
Guru Mahārāj identifies this

30
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:42,320
as the first conception of Kṛṣṇa
of the upper world,

31
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:48,820
of the spiritual domain,
but not accompanied by His potency.

32
00:02:48,820 --> 00:02:53,490
Bhagavān in earnest means
Lakṣmī–Nārāyaṇa, Sītā–Rāma,

33
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:56,400
Rukmiṇī–Dvārakādhīśa,

34
00:02:56,400 --> 00:03:00,900
and Kṛṣṇa in Mathurā, 
Vṛndāvan—

35
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:06,900
vṛndāvana haite śreṣṭhe govardhana-śaila
gāndharvikā giridhārī yathā krīḍā kailā [Pj: 3.22]

36
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:15,360
And like that. And svayaṁ bhagavān
Kṛṣṇa, at the right hand of Rādhārāṇī.

37
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:25,450
So Everest by parallel 
representing Kṛṣṇa,

38
00:03:25,450 --> 00:03:31,500
and going near, coming in connection 
with those surrounding Everest.

39
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:38,230
So, Kṛṣṇa conception
sākṣād-dharitvena samasta-śāstrair,

40
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:44,500
but then this interesting shift
takes place,

41
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:51,100
kintu prabhor yaḥ priya eva tasya
vande guroḥ śrī-caraṇāravindam

42
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:54,500
Which Guru Mahārāj
renders as ‘prabhor priya’—

43
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:59,400
it’s saying, 
“But upon a closer examination

44
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:05,310
of guru-tattva, the guru principle,
the guru conception—guru,

45
00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:13,570
we’ll see a shift takes place
from Kṛṣṇa to His potency.”

46
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:18,700
Prabhor priya—the one
who is most dear to Kṛṣṇa.

